column1: #Text=We are requested to correct an error which appeared in our last, to the effect that Mr.
#Text=Mole, chemist, of this place, had committed suicide.

#Text=The paragraph, we presume, was written by our correspondent before the inquest put a different complexion on the melancholy event, for we are given to understand the jury returned a verdict to tbe effect that Mr.
#Text=Mole " Died of disease of the heart, accelerated by taking a medicinal dose of prussic acid."

#Text=The unfortunate gentleman suffered from palpitation of the heart, and it appears the dilution which he took, instead of tending to allay the symptoms, actually aggravated the case, and a fatal end was the result.
#Text=—On Thursday last the parish church of Over Stowey, near this place, having undergone restoration, was re-opened for Divine worship.
#Text=The chancel of the church is now lighted by two beautiful corona manufactured by Singer, of Frome, which was the gift of tbe Right Rev.
#Text=Bishop Toxer. of the Central African mission.
#Text=The preachers at the services were the Rev.
#Text=Lake, prebendary of Wells, and vicar of Huntspill, and the Rev.
#Text=The event was the occasion of much rejoicing, and between the services a substantial dinner was given to the working men of the parish, which was presided over by the Right Hon.
#Text=Walpole in the chair, on Thursday appointed the committee to hear the petitions against the return for this borough.
#Text=There are two petitions, the first being against the return of Mr.
#Text=Westropp, on the ground of bribery, treating, and undue influence, and the second against Mr.
#Text=Durrant Cooper appeared in support of the first petition; and Mr.
#Text=Spofforth in support of the second petition; and Mr.
#Text=No objection was made to the selection.
